    "response_text": "Certainly! I'll explain how a binary search algorithm works in detail.\n\n### What is Binary Search?\n\nBinary search is an efficient algorithm for finding an item from a sorted list of items. It works by repeatedly dividing in half the portion of the list that could contain the item, until you've narrowed down the possible locations to just one.\n\n### Key Characteristics\n\n- **Sorted List**: The list must be sorted in ascending or descending order.\n- **Efficiency**: It has a time complexity of O(log n), making it very efficient for large datasets.\n\n### How Binary Search Works\n\n1. **Initialization**:\n   - Start with the middle element of the entire list.\n   - If the target value matches the middle element, the search is complete.\n   - If the target value is less than the middle element, repeat the process on the left half of the list.\n   - If the target value is greater than the middle element, repeat the process on the right half of the list.\n\n2.",
